SIMPLE: erector
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Erector
<hw>E*rec"tor</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, erects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>A muscle which raises any
part.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>An attachment to a microscope,
telescope, or other optical instrument, for making the image erect
instead of inverted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Erelong</ent>⟦br⟧
